The paper proposes a model for link prediction in dynamic social networks, which involves both social network analysis and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also presents a global optimization algorithm and two alternative optimization algorithms, which are related to machine learning and optimization, respectively. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. In addition, the paper focuses on the scalability of the proposed model, which is related to the management and processing of large datasets, and thus cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possible category. The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed model compared to existing approaches, which involves experimental evaluation and statistical analysis, and thus cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also possible categories.
